    fullDescription: "Estate Romana ('Roman Summer') is not a single event but a sprawling, city-wide programme of cultural happenings that transforms Rome through the hot months from June to September, turning the whole city into an open-air stage after dark and giving the summer a festive lift despite the heat. The offering is huge and varied: open-air cinema seasons, most famously the screenings on the Isola del Cinema on Tiber Island, where a pop-up riverside village of bars, food stalls and a big screen springs up between the bridges; classical and pop concerts; theatre and dance; art exhibitions; literary evenings; and food and craft markets in parks and piazzas across the city. A summer highlight is the Rome Opera's season of grand open-air productions staged among the floodlit ruins of the Baths of Caracalla, an unforgettable setting for opera and ballet under the stars, and Ostia Antica's ancient theatre likewise hosts performances. The banks of the Tiber come alive with the Lungo il Tevere festival, a long ribbon of pop-up bars, restaurants, stalls and entertainment along the river. Many events are free and others reasonably ticketed. It is the perfect antidote to sweltering days: rest in the afternoon, then head out on balmy evenings to enjoy the culture, the riverside atmosphere and the buzz. Check the official Estate Romana programme for what is on during your visit.",
